model.scoring_formula:
PER-TRANSACTION risk_score, fully recomputable from source fields (only rows with amount>=100000 are scored; below that is out of model scope):

STEP 1 — Compute each FAMILY's contribution = the GREATEST severity tier that fires within that family (0 if none). Family predicates and tier weights are the specialists' calibrated SQL (exact-equality categories, word-BOUNDARY name logic only — never substring — to preclude the Aztec/ZTE class):
  f_round      = GREATEST over {round_1m=5 , round_100k_not1m=4 , whole_not10k=3}
  f_dup        = GREATEST over {diffday_disc=5 , sameday_disc_ext=3 , diffday_all=2}
  f_conc       = GREATEST over {sole_source_>=20%_disc=4 , dependency_>=33%=2}
  f_newvendor  = GREATEST over {dominant_new=5 , short_tenure_JV=4 , large_first=3}  ; THEN if fiscal_year=2021: f_newvendor = floor(f_newvendor/2)  (FY21 post-gap artifact down-weight)
  f_yearend    = GREATEST over {p13_disc=4 , p13_all=3 , june_round_disc=3}
  f_peer       = {z>=20 & ac_n>=8 & non-entitlement = 4 , else 0}
  f_account    = GREATEST over {triple_gap=5 , placeholder_payee_disc=4 , no_contract_named=2 , offcontract_base=2}
  f_rail       = GREATEST over {manual_disc=4 , manual_nonentitlement=3 , null_or_warrant_disc=2}
  f_entity     = GREATEST over {person_name_disc=3 , masked_payee_extrail_disc=3}
  f_benford    = {agency in 5-name list & non-entitlement = 2 , else 0}

STEP 2 — Cross-family DEDUP (subsume same-fact double counts):
  IF triple_gap fired (f_account=5):  f_rail := 0  AND  drop the masked-payee external-rail entity case from f_entity   (the rail + missing-payee facts are the components of the triple gap)
  Off-contract nested tiers contribute 0 (their concentration/peer/contract facts already live in f_conc / f_peer / f_account).

STEP 3 — marker_sum = f_round + f_dup + f_conc + f_newvendor + f_yearend + f_peer + f_account + f_rail_net + f_entity_net + f_benford
         (magnitude and category are NOT summed here — they modulate, not add.)

STEP 4 — risk_score = marker_sum * category_risk_multiplier(category1)
         where the multiplier is the documented CASE map (DEBT 0.3 ; AID 0.4 ; TRANSFERS OUT 0.4 ; COST ALLOC 0.5 ; CONVERSION 0.5 ; PERSONAL SVCS 0.7 ; EMPLOYEE-RELATED 0.9 ; FOOD 0.9 ; TRAVEL 1.0 ; N/A 1.0 ; NULL 1.0 ; NON-CAP EQUIP 1.2 ; CAP EQUIP 1.2 ; CAP OUTLAY 1.3 ; OTHER OPERATING 1.4 ; PROF & OUTSIDE SVCS 1.5).

This is the ONLY place dollars/category enter the SCORE; the mag_band itself is reserved for the Tier matrix axis so a large amount alone can never manufacture a high score. Verified distribution on 306,604 rows: 83.6% score 0 (clean), avg 0.87, p90 3.0, p95 7.0, p99 11.2, max 30.0. Mega-transfers validate: $4.66B TRANSFERS OUT -> 0.0 ; $318M AID firing 3 marker pts -> 1.2 (LOW). Thin years FY19/20 show the LOWEST fire rate (14-16%) because vid/fp/appr-dependent families self-suppress — graceful degradation, never a penalty for a system-wide-absent field.
